WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.500
God's grace is sufficient.

00:00:01.500 --> 00:00:03.319
Second Corinthians 12 and verse number nine,

00:00:03.319 --> 00:00:04.260
the banners have been there.

00:00:04.260 --> 00:00:06.019
We sing about it in our theme song,

00:00:06.019 --> 00:00:08.300
God's grace is sufficient.

00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:10.300
And what a blessing in that song,

00:00:10.300 --> 00:00:13.979
they talked about burdens and all of us have burdens

00:00:13.979 --> 00:00:15.920
that we carry at some point in our lives.

00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:17.260
And here's what our great God,

00:00:17.260 --> 00:00:19.020
who is the God of all comfort said,

00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:24.020
cast your burden upon the Lord and he shall sustain thee.

00:00:24.260 --> 00:00:26.579
Casting all your care upon him, why?

00:00:26.579 --> 00:00:28.739
For he careth for you.

00:00:28.739 --> 00:00:30.579
Isn't it good to know the Bible

00:00:30.579 --> 00:00:32.180
and to know the God of the Bible,

00:00:32.180 --> 00:00:34.979
the truth that God has given to us in his word.

00:00:34.979 --> 00:00:36.619
And I'm thankful this morning

00:00:36.619 --> 00:00:39.700
that he is the God of all comfort.

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:43.459
And he comforted us in all of our time of difficulty,

00:00:43.459 --> 00:00:47.540
tribulation, trial, and we just rejoice in that,

00:00:47.540 --> 00:00:49.979
certainly appreciate that song this morning.

00:00:49.979 --> 00:00:51.180
If you have your Bible with you,

00:00:51.180 --> 00:00:53.580
Second Corinthians chapter number 11,

00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:55.979
and with God's help this morning,

00:00:55.979 --> 00:00:57.500
we're gonna get through 15 verses.

00:00:57.500 --> 00:00:58.939
I thought we'd do this in two weeks,

00:00:58.939 --> 00:01:02.020
but just looking at things as we try to wrap up

00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:03.900
studying through the book of Second Corinthians

00:01:03.900 --> 00:01:05.819
here in 2025.

00:01:05.819 --> 00:01:08.180
And so I'm excited about what God has for us.

00:01:08.180 --> 00:01:09.860
God's word is profitable

00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:12.599
and I'm thankful that he's given it to us.

00:01:12.599 --> 00:01:14.940
And here in the text, remember in chapter 10,

00:01:14.940 --> 00:01:16.620
we studied it last week,

00:01:16.620 --> 00:01:19.099
that Paul informed the believers in Corinth

00:01:19.099 --> 00:01:23.139
of his singular desire for his life.

00:01:23.139 --> 00:01:23.980
What was it?

00:01:23.980 --> 00:01:25.339
To please God.

00:01:25.339 --> 00:01:28.379
I mean, his only desire in life

00:01:28.379 --> 00:01:31.139
was that he would please God.

00:01:31.139 --> 00:01:34.019
By the way, that should be the single desire

00:01:34.019 --> 00:01:35.620
of every child of God,

00:01:35.620 --> 00:01:38.260
that we would live our lives in such a way

00:01:38.260 --> 00:01:40.260
that he would smile upon us,

00:01:40.260 --> 00:01:42.059
that he would be pleased with us,

00:01:42.059 --> 00:01:44.660
that we would not seek to,

00:01:44.660 --> 00:01:46.180
as he said at the end of the chapter,

00:01:46.180 --> 00:01:47.980
not seek to commend ourselves,

00:01:47.980 --> 00:01:51.019
but to have the Lord's commendation.

00:01:51.019 --> 00:01:52.819
And what a blessing that is.

00:01:52.819 --> 00:01:55.059
I'm thankful as you study through the scriptures

00:01:55.779 --> 00:01:58.459
that if you're saved by the grace of God this morning,

00:01:58.459 --> 00:02:01.419
what a joy to know that heaven is our home.

00:02:01.419 --> 00:02:05.339
And if you understand the truth that we could hear,

00:02:05.339 --> 00:02:09.259
well done thou good and faithful servant.

00:02:09.259 --> 00:02:11.100
The apostle Paul was not a prideful man,

00:02:11.100 --> 00:02:13.500
but the apostle Paul knew who he had believed

00:02:13.500 --> 00:02:16.740
and he knew the truth of salvation and of eternity.

00:02:16.740 --> 00:02:19.259
And he knew that he'd stand before the Lord

00:02:19.259 --> 00:02:20.339
to be absent from the body,

00:02:20.339 --> 00:02:22.580
was to be present with the Lord.

00:02:22.580 --> 00:02:24.940
And he said that he knew he had finished his course,

00:02:25.820 --> 00:02:26.979
he'd run his race, he did what he was supposed to do,

00:02:26.979 --> 00:02:28.619
he kept the faith.

00:02:28.619 --> 00:02:30.339
And he said there was a crown of righteousness

00:02:30.339 --> 00:02:33.059
laid up for him, but not for him only,

00:02:33.059 --> 00:02:34.899
but for all those that love his appearing.

00:02:34.899 --> 00:02:38.539
And what a blessing to know the truth of God's word.

00:02:38.539 --> 00:02:41.500
It's our desire that we would live in such a way

00:02:41.500 --> 00:02:43.619
that he would be pleased with our lives.

00:02:43.619 --> 00:02:45.179
If you're saved this morning,

00:02:45.179 --> 00:02:48.539
the reality is that we will live with him forever.

00:02:48.539 --> 00:02:51.100
And the question, as we've said multiple times,

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:53.860
as we've studied here through the book of 2 Corinthians,

00:02:54.300 --> 00:02:57.740
is simply this, will we live for him

00:02:57.740 --> 00:03:00.460
until that day that we live with him?

00:03:00.460 --> 00:03:03.339
And that's the great question as we consider our lives.

00:03:03.339 --> 00:03:05.940
As you can continue studying through here

00:03:05.940 --> 00:03:07.259
in the book of 2 Corinthians,

00:03:07.259 --> 00:03:09.259
we come to this 11th chapter,

00:03:09.259 --> 00:03:12.979
and the apostle Paul will continue to address the matter

00:03:12.979 --> 00:03:14.979
that is taking place there in Corinth.

00:03:14.979 --> 00:03:16.860
And you know, I mentioned it several times

00:03:16.860 --> 00:03:19.820
as we've studied here through the book of 2 Corinthians,

00:03:19.820 --> 00:03:22.500
but Paul was used of God to go to Corinth

00:03:22.539 --> 00:03:24.979
to see a church established.

00:03:24.979 --> 00:03:28.059
And then there were some false teachers that came in,

00:03:28.059 --> 00:03:31.520
Judaizers, and these false teachers came in,

00:03:31.520 --> 00:03:33.479
and there's conflict that results

00:03:33.479 --> 00:03:35.220
because of their false teaching.

00:03:35.220 --> 00:03:37.539
Not only do they bring in false teaching,

00:03:37.539 --> 00:03:40.699
but they also criticize Paul.

00:03:40.699 --> 00:03:44.539
And they're criticizing Paul and his ministry

00:03:44.539 --> 00:03:45.720
and so on and so forth.

00:03:45.720 --> 00:03:48.740
And so the apostle Paul, beginning in chapter 10,

00:03:48.740 --> 00:03:51.380
and as we continue here in chapter number 11,

00:03:51.380 --> 00:03:55.380
is providing them with some explanation, if you will,

00:03:55.380 --> 00:03:59.380
and seeking to help them understand what is taking place

00:03:59.380 --> 00:04:00.440
and really the truth.

00:04:00.440 --> 00:04:03.380
We find in verse number one of 2 Corinthians 11,

00:04:03.380 --> 00:04:04.199
the Bible says,

00:04:04.199 --> 00:04:08.619
would to God, you could bear with me a little in my falling

00:04:08.619 --> 00:04:11.259
and indeed bear with me.

00:04:11.259 --> 00:04:15.300
For I am jealous over you with godly jealousy,

00:04:15.300 --> 00:04:17.619
for I have espoused you to one husband

00:04:17.619 --> 00:04:21.779
that I may present you as a chaste virgin to Christ,

00:04:21.779 --> 00:04:23.059
but I fear,

00:04:24.619 --> 00:04:26.260
but I fear,

00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:28.260
lest by any means,

00:04:28.260 --> 00:04:32.420
as the serpent beguiled Eve through his subtlety,

00:04:32.420 --> 00:04:35.420
so your mind should be corrupted

00:04:35.420 --> 00:04:39.559
from the simplicity that is in Christ.

00:04:39.559 --> 00:04:42.700
For if he that cometh preacheth another Jesus

00:04:42.700 --> 00:04:44.220
whom we have not preached,

00:04:44.220 --> 00:04:46.260
or if you receive another spirit

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:47.399
which you have not received,

00:04:48.140 --> 00:04:50.119
or another gospel which you have not accepted,

00:04:50.119 --> 00:04:51.880
you might well bear with him.

00:04:51.880 --> 00:04:53.880
We'll continue through verse 15

00:04:53.880 --> 00:04:56.279
as we get through the text this morning.

00:04:56.279 --> 00:04:58.320
I read those few verses by way of introduction.

00:04:58.320 --> 00:05:01.359
I've titled the message this morning, Beware of Dogs.

00:05:01.359 --> 00:05:02.839
Isn't that an interesting text?

00:05:02.839 --> 00:05:03.660
And really it is,

00:05:03.660 --> 00:05:05.000
because over in the book of Philippians,

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:07.640
when Paul is referring to the Judaizers

00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:09.079
in Philippians three and verse number two

00:05:09.079 --> 00:05:10.399
to that church in Philippi,

00:05:10.399 --> 00:05:13.320
by which we find that it's that church

00:05:13.320 --> 00:05:15.899
that communicated with Paul once and again,

00:05:15.899 --> 00:05:18.519
even while he was ministering in Corinth,

00:05:18.519 --> 00:05:20.619
that he says to those believers in Philippi

00:05:20.619 --> 00:05:21.980
in Philippians three and verse two,

00:05:21.980 --> 00:05:23.820
beware of dogs,

00:05:23.820 --> 00:05:25.980
beware of evil workers,

00:05:25.980 --> 00:05:28.739
beware of the concision.

00:05:28.739 --> 00:05:30.220
We look at this text of scripture

00:05:30.220 --> 00:05:31.980
and it really reminds me of the question

00:05:31.980 --> 00:05:34.720
that Jesus asked to his disciples

00:05:34.720 --> 00:05:37.540
when he took them in Matthew chapter 16

00:05:37.540 --> 00:05:39.059
to Caesarea Philippi.

00:05:39.059 --> 00:05:40.540
And he took them to Caesarea Philippi

00:05:40.540 --> 00:05:41.660
and as he takes them there

00:05:41.660 --> 00:05:44.359
and it's a place that was known

00:05:44.359 --> 00:05:46.559
as being the gates of hell

00:05:46.559 --> 00:05:48.160
and all of the false teaching

00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:49.359
that was prevalent there

00:05:49.359 --> 00:05:50.279
and I've been there,

00:05:50.279 --> 00:05:51.119
I've seen it

00:05:51.119 --> 00:05:54.160
and I understand with a better clarity now

00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:56.839
why Jesus took them to that place

00:05:56.839 --> 00:05:59.899
and the purpose in asking them

00:05:59.899 --> 00:06:01.760
the question that he did there

00:06:01.760 --> 00:06:03.480
and it was simply this,

00:06:03.480 --> 00:06:05.839
who do men say that I am?

00:06:08.359 --> 00:06:09.880
Well, what was the answer?

00:06:09.880 --> 00:06:13.279
Well, some say that you're Jeremiah,

00:06:13.279 --> 00:06:14.880
one of the prophets,

00:06:14.880 --> 00:06:16.200
John the Baptist

00:06:17.160 --> 00:06:21.239
and Jesus says but whom say ye that I am?

00:06:21.239 --> 00:06:24.600
Peter stands as often being the one

00:06:24.600 --> 00:06:26.000
to open his mouth

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:30.000
and in this context it was a great declaration.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:31.920
There are other times that Peter says things

00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:33.579
and he even says later on

00:06:33.579 --> 00:06:35.279
I didn't know what he was saying

00:06:35.279 --> 00:06:39.000
but here he says thou art the Christ,

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:41.839
the son of the living God

00:06:41.839 --> 00:06:43.279
and this morning as we begin to look

00:06:43.279 --> 00:06:44.519
at this text of scripture

00:06:44.519 --> 00:06:46.640
and we're concerned about the false teaching

00:06:46.640 --> 00:06:47.519
and what takes place,

00:06:47.519 --> 00:06:49.320
we find that that question

00:06:49.320 --> 00:06:53.079
that Jesus asks in Matthew chapter 16,

00:06:53.079 --> 00:06:55.880
the question regarding who Jesus is

00:06:55.880 --> 00:06:57.440
has always been

00:06:58.619 --> 00:07:01.100
and will always be

00:07:01.100 --> 00:07:03.239
the most important question

00:07:03.239 --> 00:07:05.720
and it is absolutely imperative

00:07:05.720 --> 00:07:08.799
that that question is answered properly.

00:07:08.799 --> 00:07:10.000
Who was Jesus?

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:12.239
He's a man.

00:07:12.239 --> 00:07:13.679
He's more than a man.

00:07:13.679 --> 00:07:14.720
He's a prophet.

00:07:14.720 --> 00:07:16.720
He's more than a prophet.

00:07:16.720 --> 00:07:18.200
He's God.

00:07:18.200 --> 00:07:19.799
He is the God man

00:07:19.799 --> 00:07:21.640
and we begin to understand

00:07:21.640 --> 00:07:24.239
that as Paul is focusing here

00:07:24.239 --> 00:07:26.519
and as you begin to understand false teaching,

00:07:26.519 --> 00:07:28.399
generally speaking,

00:07:28.399 --> 00:07:29.839
almost every cult,

00:07:29.839 --> 00:07:31.559
almost every false religion,

00:07:31.559 --> 00:07:32.559
you know where they get it wrong?

00:07:32.559 --> 00:07:34.959
They get it wrong on Jesus.

00:07:34.959 --> 00:07:36.720
They get it wrong on Jesus

00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:39.200
and if you get it wrong on Jesus,

00:07:39.200 --> 00:07:41.440
all of eternity is at stake.

00:07:42.959 --> 00:07:44.200
The enemy has no problem

00:07:44.200 --> 00:07:46.600
with believing that Jesus is a man.

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:47.720
The enemy has no problem

00:07:47.720 --> 00:07:50.079
with believing that Jesus is a prophet.

00:07:50.079 --> 00:07:50.920
He's a good man.

00:07:50.920 --> 00:07:51.760
He did good things.

00:07:51.760 --> 00:07:53.839
The enemy has no problem with that

00:07:53.839 --> 00:07:55.040
but what the enemy has a problem with

00:07:55.040 --> 00:07:57.559
is when they say Jesus is God

00:07:57.559 --> 00:08:00.760
and he is the savior of the world.

00:08:00.760 --> 00:08:02.279
As we look at the context here,

00:08:02.279 --> 00:08:03.559
we find if you're taking notes,

00:08:03.559 --> 00:08:05.440
I only have two points this morning.

00:08:05.440 --> 00:08:06.279
Don't get excited.

00:08:06.279 --> 00:08:07.600
It doesn't mean we're leaving early

00:08:07.600 --> 00:08:09.760
and I got some sub points this morning

00:08:09.760 --> 00:08:11.160
but just two thoughts this morning

00:08:11.160 --> 00:08:12.160
as we look at this text.

00:08:12.160 --> 00:08:14.119
Number one, reference with me

00:08:14.119 --> 00:08:18.559
or notice with me the explanation of Paul.

00:08:18.559 --> 00:08:19.839
In the first 12 verses,

00:08:19.839 --> 00:08:22.320
I find that Paul is really providing

00:08:22.320 --> 00:08:25.359
the believers at Corinth with an explanation.

00:08:25.359 --> 00:08:28.320
He begins as we've already read the first four verses.

00:08:28.320 --> 00:08:30.880
He begins by explaining his concern.

00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:32.479
What was the concern that he had?

00:08:32.479 --> 00:08:33.719
Well, we find that as he begins

00:08:33.719 --> 00:08:36.960
to speak to these believers in Corinth,

00:08:36.960 --> 00:08:39.640
he begins to reference that early time

00:08:39.640 --> 00:08:41.080
when he first came to Corinth.

00:08:41.080 --> 00:08:43.239
You could look back at Acts chapter 18

00:08:43.239 --> 00:08:45.320
and we'll reference that in just a few minutes

00:08:45.320 --> 00:08:47.239
but we find that the apostle Paul,

00:08:47.239 --> 00:08:49.440
as he went into Corinth, what did he do?

00:08:49.440 --> 00:08:51.640
He went in preaching the gospel.

00:08:51.640 --> 00:08:52.479
Why?

00:08:52.479 --> 00:08:55.479
Because the gospel is the power of God unto salvation.

00:08:55.479 --> 00:08:57.719
By the way, the gospel is very clear.

00:08:57.719 --> 00:09:00.599
It's defined in the Bible what the gospel is.

00:09:00.599 --> 00:09:03.799
The gospel is the death, burial

00:09:03.799 --> 00:09:06.059
and resurrection of Jesus Christ.

00:09:06.059 --> 00:09:08.099
I spoke to a man last Monday

00:09:08.099 --> 00:09:11.260
and he had some crosses on some earrings.

00:09:11.260 --> 00:09:13.559
He had one in each ear and he had these crosses

00:09:13.559 --> 00:09:15.059
and I asked him this question.

00:09:15.059 --> 00:09:17.419
I said, hey, what do those crosses mean to you?

00:09:18.979 --> 00:09:21.539
It was as if no one ever asked him that question before

00:09:21.539 --> 00:09:22.979
and maybe no one had.

00:09:24.299 --> 00:09:26.219
And he said, well, he paused and he said,

00:09:26.219 --> 00:09:29.219
well, you know, it's my religion.

00:09:29.219 --> 00:09:30.179
And I said, your religion?

00:09:30.179 --> 00:09:31.099
I said, so what does that mean?

00:09:31.099 --> 00:09:33.619
He's like, you know, like the gospel.

00:09:33.619 --> 00:09:34.460
And I said, that's great.

00:09:34.460 --> 00:09:35.859
You know, what's the gospel?

00:09:40.659 --> 00:09:41.820
And there's no answer.

00:09:43.780 --> 00:09:45.780
He didn't know what the gospel was.

00:09:45.780 --> 00:09:47.299
Begin to talk to him.

00:09:47.299 --> 00:09:48.580
He was working.

00:09:48.580 --> 00:09:50.700
It's a short interaction.

00:09:50.700 --> 00:09:52.299
But I didn't tell him what the gospel is.

00:09:52.299 --> 00:09:55.200
Aren't you thankful that you know the gospel?

00:09:55.200 --> 00:09:57.380
Where would we be if we didn't know the gospel?

00:09:57.380 --> 00:10:00.219
We'd be waiting for someone else to bring us the gospel.

00:10:00.219 --> 00:10:06.219
Or, we would be blinded by the enemy, the little G, God of this world, according to 2 Corinthians 4,

00:10:06.219 --> 00:10:12.219
hath blinded the minds of them which believe not, lest the light of the glorious gospel should shine unto them.

00:10:12.219 --> 00:10:15.219
Is that not what the Bible says in 2 Corinthians chapter 4?

00:10:15.219 --> 00:10:20.219
And we find this morning that the gospel is the power of God unto salvation.

00:10:20.219 --> 00:10:22.219
Why do we preach the gospel?

00:10:22.219 --> 00:10:24.219
Why do we go forth giving the gospel?

00:10:24.219 --> 00:10:30.219
Because the gospel changes lives and I personally know the power of the gospel to change a life.

00:10:30.219 --> 00:10:32.219
And what a blessing to understand that.

00:10:32.219 --> 00:10:37.219
So Paul goes into Corinth and he's preached the gospel to them.

00:10:37.219 --> 00:10:41.219
He's voicing, he's explaining his concern for them. Why?

00:10:41.219 --> 00:10:43.219
Because he tells them in verse 2,

00:10:43.219 --> 00:10:46.219
I am jealous over you with a godly jealousy.

00:10:46.219 --> 00:10:54.219
He tells them I've espoused you to one husband, that I may present you as a chaste virgin to Christ.

00:10:54.219 --> 00:11:01.219
He's speaking about this mystery of the church and he's speaking about how the church is the bride of Christ.

00:11:01.219 --> 00:11:09.219
And he's speaking to them about when they got saved, how they became believers and they became part of the body of Christ,

00:11:09.219 --> 00:11:10.219
the bride of Christ.

00:11:10.219 --> 00:11:12.219
And what is the bride of Christ?

00:11:12.219 --> 00:11:17.219
As he says that I desire to present you as a chaste virgin to Christ.

00:11:17.219 --> 00:11:26.219
We talk about the marriage supper of the lamb and we understand some of these things that will take place in future based on prophecy.

00:11:26.219 --> 00:11:31.219
But as we live today and we understand that Paul says to the church in Ephesus,

00:11:31.219 --> 00:11:37.219
speaking of the church, that he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word.

00:11:37.219 --> 00:11:44.219
That he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot or wrinkle or any such thing,

00:11:44.219 --> 00:11:48.219
but that it should be holy and without blemish.

00:11:48.219 --> 00:11:59.219
Can I tell you this morning that there's a perception that is prevalent today that holy living isn't really that important.

00:12:00.219 --> 00:12:06.219
But we find in the Bible that the grace of God that bringeth salvation, it's appeared to all men.

00:12:06.219 --> 00:12:15.219
It teaches us that we're to live a certain way and we're to live godly and we're to live righteously and we're to live holy and soberly.

